# Patch 0018 — Kavacha command registry (ROADMAP Phase 3; PLATFORM_PLAN.md).
#
# Turns the ad-hoc Kavacha entries patch 0007 bolted onto Zen's palette into
# a real registry: KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs owns the Kavacha commands
# (tagged by domain — navigation / organization / productivity / appearance)
# and exposes register()/all(), the surface plugins and late-initializing
# features extend. ZenUBGlobalActions spreads all() into its action list and
# binds an onRegister() sink so runtime registrations land in the live
# palette (globalActions is mutated in place, which the provider reads).
#
# The six 0007 commands (template spaces, notes, archive, search) move into
# the registry unchanged; two new commands expose already-shipped features
# that had no palette entry:
#   - "Sleep Inactive Tabs Now" — KavachaTabMemory.sleepBackgroundTabsNow()
#     (new; _sweep() gained an optional forced-cutoff arg so a manual sweep
#     discards every eligible background tab regardless of the time
#     threshold; the repeating timer still calls _sweep() with no arg).
#   - "Toggle New Tab Style (Dashboard / Search)" — flips
#     zen.urlbar.replace-newtab; KavachaNewTab re-points about:newtab live.
# Restore-archived-space is intentionally omitted: it needs a picker (which
# of several archived spaces?) and has no clean single-call opener — stays
# reachable via the Archived Spaces menu. Domain-grouped display in the
# palette is a later enhancement; domain is metadata for now.
#
# Marionette-verified: 8 commands across 4 domains reach the palette with
# localized labels; runtime register() grows the live palette; sleep-tabs
# discards background tabs and spares the active one; toggle-newtab flips
# the pref and re-points about:newtab. Applies on top of 0017.
